comments_since_last_sample.body:
More underrated pieces (composers) that I like:

Kurt Atterberg: Piano Concerto
Sergei Bortkiewicz: Preludes Op.33 and Piano Sonata 2
Georgy Catoire: 4 Pieces Op.12
Oleg Eiges: Piano Sonata No.4 “Sonata-Toccata”
Samuil Feinberg: Piano Sonata No.3
César Franck: Violin Sonata
Alberto Ginastera: Suite de danzas criollas 
Alexander Glazunov: Piano Concerto No.2 
Reinhold Glière: Symphonies (He wrote 3) and Harp Concerto
Leopold Godowsky: Java Suite
Friedrich Gulda: Play Piano Play and Prelude and Fugue
Johann Nepomuk Hummel: Piano Concerto No.2 and 3
Vasily Kalinnikov: Symphony No.1 and 2
Zoltán Kodály: Sonata for unaccompanied Cello
Erich Wolfgang Korngold: Piano Quintet
Rued Langgaard: Sfærernes Musik and Symphony No.1
Franz Liszt: Sancta Dorothea, Csárdas
Sergei Lyapunov: Transcendental Etudes, Barcarolle, Piano Sonata and Symphony No.1 and 2
Albéric Magnard: Symphony No.4
Nikolai Medtner: Piano Concerti (He wrote 3, all are amazing)
Erkki Melartin: Symphony No.3
Darius Milhaud: String Quartet No.1
Nikolai Myaskovsky: Symphony No.25
Walter Niemann: Piano Sonata No.1
Leo Ornstein: Piano Sonata No.4 and Cello Sonata No.2
Selim Palmgren: Piano Sonata, Piano Concerto No.2, Op.54 and Op.57 no.2 „Raindrops“
Wilhelm Peterson-Berger: Symphony No.3, Frösöblomster
Max Reger: Träume am Kamin, Variations and Fugue on Bach
Ottorino Respighi: Concerto in Modo Misolidio, 6 Pieces for piano
Xaver Scharwenka: Piano Concerti (All 4 are really good)
Robert Schumann: Requiem in D-Flat
Alexander Scriabin: Valse Op.38, Fantasy Op.28, Piano Sonata No.8, Symphonies (All 3 + Op.54 and Op.60 are amazing)
Josef Suk: Asrael Symphony
Alexei Stanchinsky: Piano Sonata No.2
Wilhelm Stenhammar: 3 Fantasies
Karol Szymanowski: Preludes Op.1 and Métopes Op.28
Emil von Sauer: Piano Concerto No.1 
Mieczysław Weinberg: Piano Sonata No.4
Felix Weingartner: Cello Concerto
Alexander von Zemlinsky: String Quartet No.1 and 2

Maybe I will add new ones later. Enjoy! All the pieces are on YouTube :)
